After years of trashing alternative media, which exposed the veteran CBS News reporters monumental Memogate fraud in 2004, Rather has joined the ranks of pajama-clad online broadcasters.

The 86-year-old grandfather of fake news now uses Facebook, YouTube and Twitter to stoke the lefts anti-Trump resistance  all while clinging bitterly to the vestiges of his defunct legendary newsman persona.

Consider Gunga Dans comments on the House Intelligence Committees release of the four-page Nunes memo alleging domestic surveillance abuses by politicized FBI brass working with Democratic operatives.

Most respectable analysts, Rather asserted, have determined that the contents of the memo are thin.